CGW has requested I present this claim for reconsideration given there was no payment, primarily due to the CBB value used in the calculation.
In the case of this GAP claim, the vehicle was purchased as a used vehicle, so we suggest it would have been appropriate to use the Average CBB valuation.  It should be noted that this insured was only on risk for approximately 3 weeks before the Total Loss.  There was only one withdrawal for the financing of this vehicle, which was for the amount of $141.24 before the Total Loss.  If the Average CBB value for this vehicle is used, we get $21,575 x HST = $24,379.75.
The LTV is within 130%, and we do not have any evidence of any Extended Warranty refunds, so according to the calculation that was derived from the GAP Claim worksheet, we arrive at a revised GAP payout of $778.07.  Given that there was only one small payment made to the loan, and given what the policy wordings state, we believe this is a fair settlement for consideration.
Please review and let us know if you are in agreement.
I look forward to hearing from you.
Thank you,
Michael
